owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params._orderInfo: Url to the encoded order data stored in IPFS

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

devdoc.title: Main contract that contains all functionality of the smart contract

acceptOrder(uint256).notice: Delivery service accepts an order.         The order needs to be approved by the seller.

approveOrder(uint256,string,string,uint2.notice: A seller approves an order.         Can be called only by the seller and the order needs to be pending.

cancelOrder(uint256).notice: An order is cancelled by the client.         Can be called only by the client.         The order needs to be pending and not yet accepted by the seller.

completeOrder(uint256).notice: An order is delivered by the delivery service to the client.         Can be called only by the delivery service or the client.         The endpoint needs to be called by both parties to reach the consensus and move the order state to Completed.

getOrdersByClient(address).notice: Gets all order ids of the client by the provided address.

getOrdersByDeliveryService(address).notice: Gets all order ids of the delivery service by the provided address.

getOrdersBySeller(address).notice: Gets all order ids of the seller by the provided address.

placeOrder(address,string,uint256).notice: A client places an order to the smart contract.

rejectOrder(uint256).notice: An order is rejected by the seller.         The order needs to be pending and not yet be accepted by the seller.

transferOrder(uint256).notice: An order is passed on to the delivery service by the seller.         Can be called only by the seller or the delivery service.         The endpoint needs to be called by both parties to reach the consensus and move the order state to InTransit.
